<br>
I believe a GM changed it at his request. (It was a bit nonRP.)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hehehehe, I remember this!  I was one of the people, along with Valkiri, that endorsed Spartax into the League of Shadows.  Back then, he originally had a.... umm... mildly lewd name LMAO.  It was one of those names that when you said it out loud it sounded trashy. LOL <br>
<br>
His original name kinda turned several LoS members off (or at least made half of them snicker), but the fact is that Spartax had always been a decent RPer not to mention a generally decent and respectable guy. Everyone agreed that he had the right qualities to be in the guild.  So it was suggested that he might petition a GM for a name change.  And presto!  He got name changed quickly, and I think the GM changed it for free.  And for the most part, he has remained with the LoS family ever since.  <br>
<br>
So yes, happy endings do happen.  I suggest going this route first.  Try to get a GM to change the name via petition (which is free). <br>
